Brute force shortest distance

G is graph

shortestDistance(G, source, target):
    path = {} //list (preserves order) with set operations for add and remove
    return shortestDistance(G, source, target, 0, path)

//Helper function
shortestDistance(G, source, target, priorDist, path):
    if source == target:
        return priorDist //could also return path
    else:

        for every outgoing edge (source, neighbor) with distance d:
            if neighbor not in path
                add neighbor to path //dropping a breadcrumb
                distance = shortestDist(G, neighbor, target, priorDist + d, path)
                remove neighbor from path //pick up breadcrumb
                if distance < shortest:
                    shortest = distance


This brute force method is O(d^n) for sparse case (where every vertex has a max of d edges) and O(n!) for dense case